http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Essay-contest/article14010758.ece

The postgraduate and research department of zoology attached to Fatima Mata National College invites entries for the annual T. Shahul Hameed Environmental Essay Competition, 2016, on “Climate change: the new Paris agreement and its likely Impact.” Essays not exceeding six A4-size pages can be submitted in English or Malayalam. Undergraduate and postgraduate students of all colleges in the State can participate. The first prize winner will be given a cash prize of Rs.5,000 and the second prize winner, Rs.2,500. All entries should reach Prof. Mary Teresa Miranda, Zoology Department, Fatima Mata National College, Kollam 691 001. For details, contact 9495974828.